original: Berggren, Tage Anton Valdemar, kyrkoherde. Köpingsvik, Tingsdal, f. 17/9/04 i M Örby långa, Kalmar 1., av Fritz B. o. Jenny Andersson. G. 34 m. Essy Bengtsson. Barn: Ingemar f. 35, Bengt 36, Gunnel 38, Kerstin 40, Lars 41, Hans 43. — Stud:ex. i Kalmar 26, teol. fil. ex. i Lund 29, teol. kand., prakt. teol. prov o. prästv. f. Växjö stift 33. V. pastor i Vickleby 33-35, kommin. där 35-43, kyrkoh. i Köping o. Ekby sed. 43. Var i Vickleby bl. a. ordf. i kyrkostämma, skolstyr. o. RK-krets. Ordf. i Köpings o. Egbys kyrkost. samt i pastoratskyrkost., ordf. i båda skolstyr. Pensionsstyr. ombud för Ölands-omr.
translated: Berggren, Tage Anton Valdemar, parish priest. Köpingsvik, Tingsdal, born on September 17th, 1904 in M Örby långa, Kalmar County, the son of Fritz B. and Jenny Andersson. Married in 1934 to Essy Bengtsson. Children: Ingemar born in 1935, Bengt in 1936, Gunnel in 1938, Kerstin in 1940, Lars in 1941, and Hans in 1943. He graduated from high school in Kalmar in 1926, and received a degree in theology from Lund University in 1929. He passed practical theology exams and was ordained as a priest in the Växjö diocese in 1933. He served as a vicar in Vickleby from 1933 to 1935, and as a curate there from 1935 to 1943. He then served as a parish priest in Köping and Ekby from 1943 onwards. He served as chairman of the church meeting, school board, and RK circuit in Vickleby, and as chairman of the church meeting, school board, and parish church meeting in Köping and Ekby. He also served as a representative for the Öland area on the Pension Board.
